---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy"
  description="What this site collects: aggregate page counts via Plausible, no cookies, nothing on the recovery pages. What the tool collects: nothing, because there is no server."
>
  <div class="wrap prose">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>Privacy</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Short version: this site counts pages, not people, and the recovery
        pages count nothing at all.
      </p>

      <h2>This website</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Analytics are <a href="https://plausible.io">Plausible</a>, a
          privacy-respecting counter that uses no cookies and collects no
          personal data, so there is no consent banner because there is nothing
          to consent to.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The recovery pages carry no analytics at all.</strong>
          <a href="/recover">/recover</a> and its Windows variant load no
          analytics script, no fonts from third parties, nothing that phones
          anywhere. A grieving person's visit is not data.
        </li>
        <li>There are no accounts, no forms and no newsletter, so this site holds no personal information about you.</li>
        <li>Articles may contain affiliate links, disclosed on the page; what a merchant collects after you click is governed by their policy, not ours.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The tool</h2>
      <p>
        Executor File the tool runs entirely on your machine. Nothing leaves it:
        no server, no account, no telemetry, no sync. The scripts work with the
        network unplugged, and the register they produce is yours, encrypted,
        on your own storage.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Anything unclear, ask in the open:{' '}
        <a href="https://github.com/TheWayWithin/executor-file/issues">GitHub issues</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
